Dear friends...

If you heard a sigh of relief in this distance, that was probably me. After many
hours of hard learning, with trial and error being the main learning method, I'm
pleased to announce that the Orthodox Peace Fellowship finally has a functioning
Web site. I realize that everyone receiving this note is a Web user, but if you
are among those who are, please take note of the Website address:

http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/jim_forest/

Computers are unforgiving machines. If you leave out even one forward slash or
any other punctuation mark, you won't find us.

Your comments and suggestions about the improvement of the OPF Web page would be
more than welcome.

If you're motivated to help make it a better looking site, I'm a total amateur
at this kind of thing and would welcome the help of anyone more skilled.

Note I'm using a CompuServe address that is mainly set up for personal pages and
which will cost $20 a month. A plus about a CompuServe address is that by all
accounts it normally offers fast access. If you are better informed than I am
about Web matters, you may have a suggestion for a different/better/cheaper
site. I'm listening to your every word.

If you happen to be running a Web page, consider establishing a link with the
OPF page. You'll note we have a short list of links on the OPF page, including
several that offer sites much more complete links to other (chiefly Orthodox)
sites. You may have a suggestion or two about other links that should be offered
at the OPF site.

Jim Forest

